						<h4>Purpose</h4>
						<p>Buying physical copies of Boom Bap Hip Hop has become somewhat a culture, and there are a lot of people throughout the world that still do it today. The problem is that physical copies are hard to find these days since people have flooded to digital platforms. People like Pedro do not like streaming their music because it takes away the feeling of being able to touch a new album and making an actual physical effort to play it.<br><br></p>
					    <p>What we do at BB Tapes is link a client’s digital album purchase to their account. For instance, if they buy Rakim’s latest album on iTunes or other globally recognized platforms, they have an option to get the physical copy through us. Even if the physical copy does not exist, the fact that the client has bought the album already allows us to make them a copy and only charge them for packaging. They have an option to have their music on vinyl, cassette or compact disc; and each format has its own price.</p>
